<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="jn0022a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="jn0" href="#jn0022">JN0: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/jn0all.htm#jn0022a"> (I.A) 22(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <p class="epiplace">[In Mullingar: an evening <br>in autumn] </p> <p class="epidial">The Lame Beggar &mdash; (<i>gripping his stick</i>)&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. It was <br>you called out after me yesterday. </p> <p class="epidial">The Two Children &mdash; (<i>gazing at him</i>)&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. No, sir. </p> <p class="epidial">The Lame Beggar &mdash; O, yes it was, though&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. (<i>moving <br>his stick up and down</i>)&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. But <br>mind what I&apos;m telling you&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. <br>D&apos;ye see that stick? </p> <p class="epidial">The Two Children &mdash; Yes, sir. </p> <p class="epidial">The Lame Beggar &mdash; Well, if ye call out after me <br>any more I&apos;ll cut ye open with <br>that stick, I&apos;ll cut the livers <br>out o&apos; ye&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. (<i>explains himself</i>) <br>.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. D&apos;ye hear me? I&apos;ll cut ye <br>open. I&apos;ll cut the livers and <br>the lights out o&apos; ye. </p></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="jn0022a"><li>Stephen Hero <a href="../../ulex/ap/lexsh.htm#jn0022a">ED</a> </li><li><ms href="#jn0022a">MS Cornell, Yale 490-1</ms> </li><li>JJA 8:027,9 </li><li><a name="sh.1" href="../udra/shda.htm#sh11d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/ap/sh11d.htm#jn0022a">Draft: sh.1</a></li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: Silverman/La Hune no. XX. Joyce visited Mullingar in July 1900. This epiphany reappears in <cite>Stephen Hero</cite> (see <a href="https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.59181/page/n243/mode/2up" target="_blank">pages 245-46 of the 1956 Jonathan Cape edition</a>).</mm> </dd></dl>
